steps.description:
Write test in crates/reify-compiler/tests/boundary2_producer.rs: `compile_enum_forward_reference_multiple_enums` — parse source with multiple enums and structures interleaved in various orders: `"structure A { let x = Color.Red }
enum Direction { In, Out }
structure B { let y = Direction.In
  let z = Color.Red }
enum Color { Red, Green, Blue }"`. Compile, assert no error diagnostics, verify all enum access expressions compiled correctly: A.x → Value::Enum(Color, Red), B.y → Value::Enum(Direction, In), B.z → Value::Enum(Color, Red). Also assert compiled.enum_defs.len() == 2. This validates the two-pass fix handles interleaved declarations with multiple forward and backward references.
